Sentencas: Two types of lanthanum doped strontium manganite (LSM)-yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) composite cathodes were prepared, one with the finger-like straight open pores by the phase inversion tape casting, and the other with the randomly distributed tortuous pores by the conventional tape casting.
Titulo: Tailoring the pore structure of cathode supports for improving the electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A gas permeation flux of 42.5 x 10(5) Lm(-2) h(-1) was measured under a trans-membrane pressure of 0.6 bar for the former while only 10.6 x 10(5) Lm(-2) h(-1) for the latter.
Titulo: Tailoring the pore structure of cathode supports for improving the electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Fuel cells supported on the as-prepared LSM-YSZ composite cathodes were fabricated, comprising a 15 mu m thick YSZ electrolyte layer and a 20 mu m thick NiO-YSZ anode.
Titulo: Tailoring the pore structure of cathode supports for improving the electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of the fuel cells was measured using H-2 as fuels and air as oxidants.
Titulo: Tailoring the pore structure of cathode supports for improving the electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cell supported on the phase-inversion derived cathode showed a maximum power density of 362 mWcm(-2) at 850 A degrees C, while only 149 mWcm(-2) for the cell supported on the cathode formed by the conventional method.
Titulo: Tailoring the pore structure of cathode supports for improving the electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The difference in the electrochemical performance between the two cells can be attributed to the pore structure of the cathode supports.
Titulo: Tailoring the pore structure of cathode supports for improving the electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is concluded that the phase inversion tape casting provides a simple and effective approach for tailoring the pore structure of the cathode support and thus enhancing the electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Tailoring the pore structure of cathode supports for improving the electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells
